tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within normal limits except for a slightly low total cholesterol, which is not clinically concerning in isolation. Glycemic control, renal function, electrolytes, and lipid fractions (HDL, LDL, triglycerides) are all satisfactory. No laboratory evidence of acute or chronic metabolic, renal, or lipid disorder at this time.
